A fisherman for more than 40 years, El Hadj Dao Gaye represents the entire fisheries sector on the Senegal Economic and Social Council. At the World Social Forum, held in Dakar in February 2011, he was one of the initiators of a workshop to discuss the contribution of fisheries, in particular the small pelagics fishery, to food security in Africa."/>
			
			
